Â Â  . â The Commission is proposing that the Council authorise the Member States falling under the EUâs common visa, asylum and immigration policy (including Sweden) to ratify, in the interests of the Community, the Seafarersâ Identity Documents Convention of the International Labour Organisation.
The Convention does not imply any change to the Regulation governing the area, which expressly lays down exceptions from the visa requirement for civilian sea crews.
Consequently, it is unreasonable that Member States should need the Councilâs authorisation; a view obviously shared by France, which has already ratified the Convention.
